

	 
      "If you children feel the ambition, feel free to do the dishes," She said. But in her head, "You vicious little malicious brats destroyed the fictitious life I'd wish for all my life." Superstitions proceeded to obscure the fairy tale of family-life. "And you dad is always away fighing." Stop bitching. I've dealt with you preminition that we are all lazy scum. You never once mention the accomplishments we've done, nor the barriers we've over come. The tension you radiate is making my temper short. I'm about to explode.  The first line is the only thing that was said...the rest would be the thought of one of the kids. 
     

    
